## Problem & Vision

Developers scatter their essential knowledge across too many places вҖ” snippets in VS Code, prompts in chat history, commands in `.txt` files, links buried in bookmarks, docs in random folders, and templates in GitHub Gists. This creates constant context switching, lost knowledge, and inconsistent workflows.

**DevLoot** solves this by providing one fast, searchable, AI-enhanced hub for all dev knowledge and resources.

---

## Target Users

| User Type | Core Need |
|---|---|
| **Everyday Developer** | Quickly grab snippets, prompts, commands, and links |
| **AI-First Developer** | Save prompts, contexts, workflows, and system messages |
| **Content Creator / Educator** | Store code blocks, explanations, and course notes |
| **Full-Stack Builder** | Collect patterns, boilerplates, and API examples |

---

## Features

### A. Items & Item Types

Items are the core unit in DevLoot. Each item has a **type** that determines how it is displayed, stored, and accessed. Types can be system-defined (below) or user-created custom types (Pro вҖ” coming later).

Types map to one of three content modes:

- `text` вҖ” stored as string content (snippet, note, prompt, command)
- `url` вҖ” stored as a URL (link)
- `file` вҖ” stored as a file upload (file, image)

URL pattern for type pages: `/items/{type-plural}` e.g. `/items/snippets`

Items are accessible and creatable quickly via a **slide-in drawer**.

### B. Collections

Collections group items of any type. A single item can belong to multiple collections.

Examples:
- `React Patterns` вҖ” snippets, notes
- `Context Files` вҖ” files
- `Python Snippets` вҖ” snippets
- `Interview Prep` вҖ” snippets, notes, links

### C. Search

Full-text search across:
- Content
- Tags
- Title
- Type

### D. Authentication

- Email / password
- GitHub OAuth
- Powered by **NextAuth v5**

### E. General Features

- Favorite collections and items
- Pin items to top
- Recently used items
- Import code from a file
- Markdown editor for text-type items
- File upload for `file` and `image` types
- Export data as JSON or ZIP (Pro)
- Dark mode by default, light mode toggle
- Add/remove items from multiple collections
- View which collections an item belongs to
- Toast notifications for actions
- Loading skeletons for async states

### F. AI Features *(Pro only)*

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **AI Auto-Tag Suggestions** | Automatically suggest relevant tags for new items |
| **AI Summaries** | Generate a short summary of any item's content |
| **AI Explain This Code** | Plain-language explanation of a code snippet |
| **Prompt Optimizer** | Refine and improve AI prompts |

> During development, all users have access to all features.

